      "span_text": "While the origins of hypertension are unknown, several lines of evidence demonstrate that pressure natriuresis in the kidney plays a key role in the long-term regulation of arterial pressure and that arterial hypertension only occurs when the pressure natriuresis relationship in the kidney is switched to the right (guytonian hypothesis)"
